  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.event.CellEditorListener, javax.swing.event.ListSelectionListener, javax.swing.event.RowSorterListener, javax.swing.event.TableColumnModelListener, javax.swing.event.TableModelListener, javax.swing.Scrollable

    public class PluginStorageManifest
extends SortableTable
    PluginStorage manages many RegisterTable (s) and each RegisterTable stores algorithms having the same type. For example, a register table manages recommendation algorithms (recommenders) whereas another manages metrics for evaluating recommenders. This PluginStorageManifest which is the graphic user interface (GUI) allows users to manage PluginStorage. Every time PluginStorage was changed, an event PluginChangedEvent is issued and dispatched to a listener PluginChangedListener. Later on, PluginChangedListener can do some tasks in its method PluginChangedListener.pluginChanged(PluginChangedEvent). Please pay attention that such PluginChangedListener must be registered with PluginStorageManifest before to receive PluginChangedEvent.
    As a convention, this class is called plug-in storage manifest, which is really a sortable table represented by SortableTable. Note, SortableTable written by David Gilbert and Nobuo Tamemasa allows users to create and show a table which can be sorted its rows according its columns.
